00:13:19.570 --> 00:13:22.300
and streamers approach risk?

00:13:22.300 --> 00:13:25.240
Mm, I hope so.

00:13:25.240 --> 00:13:28.420
Streaming service changed
their audience as well.

00:13:28.420 --> 00:13:31.660
They want to watch real story,

00:13:31.660 --> 00:13:33.580
drama, authenticity.

00:13:34.960 --> 00:13:37.600
Shogun has turned out to
be a a huge success. Yeah.

00:13:37.600 --> 00:13:41.845
And you're trying to lean into
more global and and localized

00:13:41.845 --> 00:13:42.845
cntent.

00:13:42.845 --> 00:13:44.230
What does that mean?

00:13:44.230 --> 00:13:46.210
You know, what markets are on the table?

00:13:46.210 --> 00:13:47.290
What's off the table?

00:13:47.290 --> 00:13:50.530
Disney Plus is currently
in over 150 countries.

00:13:50.530 --> 00:13:54.910
We are not producing local
originals in all of them.

00:13:54.910 --> 00:13:58.960
We are picking key countries
in each of the regions

00:13:58.960 --> 00:14:00.970
and developing original content

00:14:00.970 --> 00:14:01.970
there.

00:14:01.970 --> 00:14:04.600
Squid Game and the Crown are
major hits like Netflix does

00:14:04.600 --> 00:14:06.370
seem to be way ahead in this area.

00:14:06.370 --> 00:14:08.020
Yeah, can you catch up?

00:14:08.020 --> 00:14:11.620
Well, I think you can. I
think you just named two shows.

00:14:11.620 --> 00:14:15.490
We had a massive hit in Korea
with a show called Movie

00:14:19.060 --> 00:14:23.140
That signed up, you know,
millions of subscribers.

00:14:23.140 --> 00:14:27.610
So absolutely the value of a hit continues

00:14:27.610 --> 00:14:28.780
to be very

00:14:28.780 --> 00:14:29.800
meaningful.

00:14:29.800 --> 00:14:32.320
You do have three separate apps
between Hulu and Disney Plus

00:14:32.320 --> 00:14:35.950
and ESPN, is a Disney super app coming.

00:14:35.950 --> 00:14:39.460
Yeah, you know what, we're
on the path to delivering

00:14:39.460 --> 00:14:41.860
that experience all in one place

00:14:41.860 --> 00:14:45.070
and making sure that
Disney Plus is a place

00:14:45.070 --> 00:14:48.730
where the environment feels
like it is personalized

00:14:48.730 --> 00:14:50.230
and specific to you.

00:14:50.230 --> 00:14:51.920
And that is the, we're moving

00:14:51.920 --> 00:14:53.600
because we think ultimately it's easier,

00:14:53.600 --> 00:14:54.950
it reduces the friction.

00:14:59.960 --> 00:15:01.520
So this is where the magic happens. Yeah.

00:15:01.520 --> 00:15:03.140
Welcome to TV animation

00:15:03.140 --> 00:15:06.320
where they do such great work
working on so many shows.

00:15:06.320 --> 00:15:10.340
It's really where the magic
starts for our youngest fans.

00:15:12.560 --> 00:15:15.260
You've spent your life on studio lots.

00:15:15.260 --> 00:15:16.400
Does it ever get old?

00:15:16.400 --> 00:15:20.450
Never. You're passing a stage

00:15:20.450 --> 00:15:25.010
where some iconic film was
shot and it's just delightful.

00:15:25.010 --> 00:15:29.690
You're reminded of an
industry that is just served

00:15:29.690 --> 00:15:32.450
for many, many years to
just entertain people.

00:15:33.470 --> 00:15:36.005
I grew up on Disney, so much Disney.

00:15:36.860 --> 00:15:40.640
My kids often go to YouTube
first. How do you change that?

00:15:40.640 --> 00:15:42.500
Well, are they going to YouTube

00:15:42.500 --> 00:15:44.300
and engaging with Disney content?

00:15:44.300 --> 00:15:47.150
'cause I will say we
have sometimes a number

00:15:47.150 --> 00:15:48.890
of channels up on YouTube.

00:15:48.890 --> 00:15:51.830
We wanna be where our fans are,

00:15:51.830 --> 00:15:56.180
and that means third party
platforms like TikTok, Instagram,

00:15:56.180 --> 00:15:57.560
obviously YouTube,

00:16:00.200 --> 00:16:02.000
Things like Bluey,
things like Coco Melon.

00:16:02.000 --> 00:16:04.550
That's not Disney ip. Does that matter?

00:16:04.550 --> 00:16:08.270
No, I think parents
enjoy it. Kids love it.

00:16:08.270 --> 00:16:11.330
But the attributes of a Disney story,

00:16:11.330 --> 00:16:12.710
beloved characters. What?

00:16:13.880 --> 00:16:17.840
It wasn't me. The music, it fits in

00:16:17.840 --> 00:16:19.670
with our ip.

00:16:19.670 --> 00:16:24.560
Every story doesn't have to be
based specifically on our ip,

00:16:24.560 --> 00:16:25.700
But all of these stories

00:16:25.700 --> 00:16:27.680
and characters could take
on a different meaning

00:16:27.680 --> 00:16:29.570
as technology brings new challenges

00:16:29.570 --> 00:16:31.820
and opportunities to the
entertainment business.

00:16:32.870 --> 00:16:34.310
I've been wanting to talk about AI.

00:16:34.310 --> 00:16:37.460
Obviously this is like
the next big disruption.

00:16:37.460 --> 00:16:40.310
This is a company that has
prided itself on storytelling

00:16:40.310 --> 00:16:41.785
for a hundred years

00:16:41.785 --> 00:16:43.915
and now a computer is getting scary,

00:16:43.915 --> 00:16:46.265
good at doing a lot of things

00:16:46.265 --> 00:16:49.100
In terms of our premium stories

00:16:49.100 --> 00:16:51.860
and how we think about ai,

00:16:51.860 --> 00:16:54.140
either bending the cost curve

00:16:54.140 --> 00:16:57.110
or helping us to be
faster, more efficient.

00:16:57.110 --> 00:16:59.960
We are approaching all of
that together with the actors,

00:16:59.960 --> 00:17:02.840
the writers, directors,
who are our partners,

00:17:02.840 --> 00:17:05.870
and have very strong feelings about

00:17:05.870 --> 00:17:08.630
what is a uniquely human story

00:17:08.630 --> 00:17:12.890
and how to protect the
contributors in that process.

00:17:12.890 --> 00:17:15.470
Bob talked about being
excited about the potential

00:17:15.470 --> 00:17:18.590
for AI generated content
on Disney plus user

00:17:18.590 --> 00:17:19.910
generated videos.

00:17:19.910 --> 00:17:21.500
Sure. That people could also watch.

00:17:21.500 --> 00:17:24.950
Is it still Disney magic
if it's AI created?

00:17:24.950 --> 00:17:27.350
Disney magic is storytelling.

00:17:27.350 --> 00:17:29.690
It doesn't have to be any one form.

00:17:29.690 --> 00:17:32.930
So I think it is the fundamentals

00:17:32.930 --> 00:17:34.970
of a story are Disney.

00:17:34.970 --> 00:17:38.180
The technology has evolved rapidly

00:17:38.180 --> 00:17:39.320
throughout the history of the company.

00:17:40.910 --> 00:17:43.550
Technology isn't the only
pressure weighing on Disney

00:17:43.550 --> 00:17:45.140
and its channels like ABC.

00:17:46.670 --> 00:17:49.590
In September, late night host
Jimmy Kimmel came under fire

00:17:49.590 --> 00:17:52.110
from the Trump administration
over remarks about Charlie

00:17:52.110 --> 00:17:54.540
Kirk's assassination. Walden

00:17:54.540 --> 00:17:55.650
and Bob Iger decided

00:17:55.650 --> 00:17:59.190
to suspend Kimmel, then a few
days later, to reinstate him.

00:18:00.360 --> 00:18:03.720
Anyway, as I was saying
before I was interrupted,

00:18:05.040 --> 00:18:07.590
The episode raised concerns
about the industry's ability

00:18:07.590 --> 00:18:09.450
to stand up for free speech

00:18:09.450 --> 00:18:11.760
and many of Hollywood's
biggest names spoke out

00:18:11.760 --> 00:18:15.930
against Kimmel's suspension. Let's talk

00:18:15.930 --> 00:18:16.930
about Kimmel.

00:18:16.930 --> 00:18:19.650
What happened and what
were the conversations

00:18:19.650 --> 00:18:21.780
between you and Bob

00:18:21.780 --> 00:18:22.780
and Jimmy?

00:18:22.780 --> 00:18:26.730
We were thinking about
only one thing as we made

00:18:26.730 --> 00:18:30.930
that decision very close to
his show going back up on

00:18:30.930 --> 00:18:32.490
that Wednesday,

00:18:32.490 --> 00:18:36.000
and that was, the situation
was extremely heated.

00:18:36.000 --> 00:18:38.190
We wanted to take the temperature down.

00:18:38.190 --> 00:18:42.180
We didn't think that was
gonna be possible that night,

00:18:42.180 --> 00:18:45.990
so we hit pause to have
conversations with Jimmy.

00:18:45.990 --> 00:18:49.500
We wanted to resolve the
situation in a certain way

00:18:49.500 --> 00:18:52.410
to protect our employees,

00:18:52.410 --> 00:18:54.930
to think about our audience.

00:18:54.930 --> 00:18:57.840
Did President Trump call
you or Bob or vice versa?

00:18:57.840 --> 00:18:59.970
Did you get any pressure
from the White House?

00:18:59.970 --> 00:19:02.370
He did not. We did not hear from them.

00:19:02.370 --> 00:19:05.100
There are reports that
cancellations of Disney Plus

00:19:05.100 --> 00:19:07.170
and Hulu spiked after the incident.

00:19:07.170 --> 00:19:08.760
How do you balance free speech

00:19:08.760 --> 00:19:12.360
and creative freedom
in a polarized climate?

00:19:12.360 --> 00:19:15.450
Well, I think those reports
were highly exaggerated.

00:19:15.450 --> 00:19:18.390
You saw the number of
subscribers that we reported

00:19:18.390 --> 00:19:19.590
during our earnings.

00:19:19.590 --> 00:19:21.570
We had a very strong quarter.

00:19:21.570 --> 00:19:25.290
I think that this issue
is firmly in our past

00:19:26.730 --> 00:19:28.140
For Walden, handling.

00:19:28.140 --> 00:19:30.330
the Kimmel crisis might
have been good practice for

00:19:30.330 --> 00:19:32.850
what could be her next role.

00:19:32.850 --> 00:19:34.350
Disney has clearly struggled

00:19:34.350 --> 00:19:36.360
with its succession planning in the past,

00:19:36.360 --> 00:19:38.880
Disney has considered a co-CEO structure

00:19:38.880 --> 00:19:40.080
to replace Bob Iger.

00:19:40.080 --> 00:19:41.610
We, what's the succession plan?

00:19:41.610 --> 00:19:43.740
What progress has been
made on a successor?

00:19:43.740 --> 00:19:46.620
Will it be someone inside
or outside? Can you share

00:19:46.620 --> 00:19:48.540
any? It'll be someone great.

00:19:48.540 --> 00:19:50.850
The biggest story in Hollywood now is

00:19:50.850 --> 00:19:53.580
who's gonna be the next CEO of Disney?

00:19:53.580 --> 00:19:57.330
And you know, there are pundits
and analysts all over TV

00:19:57.330 --> 00:20:00.570
and podcasts talking
about who's in the lead

00:20:00.570 --> 00:20:02.280
and you're one of the leading candidates.

00:20:02.280 --> 00:20:04.020
So they're often talking about you.

00:20:04.020 --> 00:20:06.510
They're often pitting you
against your colleagues.

00:20:06.510 --> 00:20:09.000
What's it been like for you on the inside?

00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:12.810
Well, being pit against my
colleagues, I don't appreciate

00:20:12.810 --> 00:20:15.420
because we have incredible relationships.

00:20:15.420 --> 00:20:17.910
We are a very tight organization,

00:20:17.910 --> 00:20:20.430
but I have enormous faith in
where this company's going.

00:20:20.430 --> 00:20:23.760
There is a world class
team at this company

00:20:23.760 --> 00:20:26.250
who is navigating the
path into the future.

00:20:27.750 --> 00:20:29.160
What is the future of Disney?

00:20:30.240 --> 00:20:32.850
The company is so big,
you might as well ask,

00:20:32.850 --> 00:20:34.410
what's the future of entertainment?

00:20:35.580 --> 00:20:37.260
It's a tricky question.

00:20:37.260 --> 00:20:39.600
What's your hope for Grey's?
Whatever happens, happens.

00:20:39.600 --> 00:20:41.610
I've long ago stopped trying to predict

00:20:41.610 --> 00:20:43.380
or hope what happens?

00:20:43.380 --> 00:20:45.960
I think the business has gotten harder

00:20:45.960 --> 00:20:49.330
and I think that there
are opportunities now

00:20:49.330 --> 00:20:50.890
and there are less slots.

00:20:50.890 --> 00:20:53.320
We have been very
traumatized by the pandemic

00:20:53.320 --> 00:20:54.670
and I think by the strikes

00:20:54.670 --> 00:20:57.640
and I think by the political climate

00:20:57.640 --> 00:21:00.310
and I sort of feel that everybody

00:21:00.310 --> 00:21:03.100
is unifying in a really beautiful way

00:21:03.100 --> 00:21:06.910
and trying to make products
that uplift and unite.

00:21:06.910 --> 00:21:10.270
You have been at the center
of so many reinventions,

00:21:10.270 --> 00:21:12.010
you know, obviously TV streaming.

00:21:12.010 --> 00:21:13.840
Now there's AI.

00:21:13.840 --> 00:21:14.890
What do you think it's gonna take

00:21:14.890 --> 00:21:18.790
to lead a hundred year old
company into the next century?

00:21:18.790 --> 00:21:20.860
Well, I think it's a lot of
the things we're doing right

00:21:20.860 --> 00:21:24.070
now, understanding the
consumer, being able

00:21:24.070 --> 00:21:26.740
to personalize experiences,

00:21:26.740 --> 00:21:31.300
building out our technology
product, creating features again

00:21:31.300 --> 00:21:33.970
that are unique to this IP

00:21:33.970 --> 00:21:38.170
that will delight people the
same way they are delighted

00:21:38.170 --> 00:21:39.430
when they go to our parks.

00:21:40.930 --> 00:21:44.080
Is the golden age of
entertainment behind us,

00:21:44.080 --> 00:21:46.000
or is the best still yet to come?

00:21:46.000 --> 00:21:47.770
Oh, I don't think it's behind us at all.

00:21:47.770 --> 00:21:50.860
I think even in a world of ai,

00:21:50.860 --> 00:21:54.670
more premium are the best stories

00:21:54.670 --> 00:21:58.000
and the best life experiences.

00:21:58.000 --> 00:21:59.590
I think we're gonna continue doing that.

00:21:59.590 --> 00:22:03.070
It's gonna mean something
to future generations

00:22:03.070 --> 00:22:05.530
and especially to parents
who wanna pass down

00:22:05.530 --> 00:22:07.450
that experience to their own kids.

00:22:07.450 --> 00:22:09.880
So the best is yet to come?
I think so, absolutely.

00:22:29.305 --> 00:22:32.885
And close. Yes. And end. And fade.

